    "comment": "Rationale: Neurabin-I is a known actin-binding protein (see Additional literature and others).\nFig.1: GFP-NrbI Is Concentrated in Dendritic Spines\nFig.2: Spine Localization of GFP-NrbI Requires the Intact Actin Cytoskeleton\n\nTogether this shows that in the postsynapse neurabin is localized to the actin cytoskeleton (hippocampal neurons).. Experimental description: - Rat neurons are used: \"Hippocampal slices were prepared from P6 or P7 rats as described\"\n- Species of overexpressed Neurabin 1 traced back to PMID:12052877 \"...were generated by PCR with full-length rat NrbI cDNA as template \"",
